WEBVTT

1.1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.769
An objection isn't a no.

1.2
00:00:03.769 --> 00:00:07.539
It's a request for a better answer.

1.3
00:00:07.539 --> 00:00:11.308
Here are the seven you'll hear most — and exactly how to answer them.

2.1
00:00:11.308 --> 00:00:16.409
Too expensive?

2.2
00:00:16.409 --> 00:00:21.509
Compare materials, then lifetimes.

2.3
00:00:21.509 --> 00:00:26.610
Compressed wood costs under a hundred rupees a square foot; SilverStone is around five hundred — for the material alone.

2.4
00:00:26.610 --> 00:00:31.711
Wood kitchens fight termites, water, and fungus, and often need replacing within five to seven years.

2.5
00:00:31.711 --> 00:00:36.811
Stone stays as good as new for decades.

2.6
00:00:36.811 --> 00:00:41.912
On lifetime cost, Magppie is usually the smarter investment.

3.1
00:00:41.912 --> 00:00:45.748
Need to think about it?

3.2
00:00:45.748 --> 00:00:49.584
Never push.

3.3
00:00:49.584 --> 00:00:53.420
Equip.

3.4
00:00:53.420 --> 00:00:57.256
Offer a short SilverStone video and installation photos on WhatsApp, a quick expert video call, or a sample sent home.

3.5
00:00:57.256 --> 00:01:01.092
Then let them choose: which would work better for you?

4.1
00:01:01.092 --> 00:01:06.394
Already have a designer?

4.2
00:01:06.394 --> 00:01:11.695
Welcome it — we collaborate with designers constantly: technical drawings, 3-D renders, seamless coordination.

4.3
00:01:11.695 --> 00:01:16.996
Many designers recommend us because SilverStone raises the value of their projects.

4.4
00:01:16.996 --> 00:01:22.298
No showroom in their city?

4.5
00:01:22.298 --> 00:01:27.600
Systems build trust: central manufacturing, trained in-house installers, written commitments, pan-India support.

4.6
00:01:27.600 --> 00:01:32.901
Never heard of Magppie?

4.7
00:01:32.901 --> 00:01:38.203
We're premium — we don't mass-market.

4.8
00:01:38.203 --> 00:01:43.504
Fifty-plus years of heritage, the Ambanis and Dhoni, and a KBIS twenty-twenty-six award.

5.1
00:01:43.504 --> 00:01:47.225
The technical three.

5.2
00:01:47.225 --> 00:01:50.945
Why not natural stone?

5.3
00:01:50.945 --> 00:01:54.666
Mining harms the environment, and granite and marble are porous — they stain and harbour bacteria.

5.4
00:01:54.666 --> 00:01:58.386
Too heavy?

5.5
00:01:58.386 --> 00:02:02.107
The cabinet structure distributes the load — no flooring impact.

5.6
00:02:02.107 --> 00:02:05.827
Brittle?

5.7
00:02:05.827 --> 00:02:09.548
Stronger than granite — the ceramic-jar drop test left it intact.

6.1
00:02:09.548 --> 00:02:12.952
Write these down.

6.2
00:02:12.952 --> 00:02:16.356
One — price objection: compare lifetimes, not stickers — wood is often replaced in five to seven years; stone is guaranteed for twenty-five.

6.3
00:02:16.356 --> 00:02:19.760
Two — need to think?

6.4
00:02:19.760 --> 00:02:23.164
Equip, never push: video, call, or sample.

6.5
00:02:23.164 --> 00:02:26.568
Three — designer?

6.6
00:02:26.568 --> 00:02:29.972
Collaborate.

6.7
00:02:29.972 --> 00:02:33.376
No showroom?

6.8
00:02:33.376 --> 00:02:36.780
Systems.

6.9
00:02:36.780 --> 00:02:40.184
Unknown brand?

6.10
00:02:40.184 --> 00:02:43.588
Premium positioning.

6.11
00:02:43.588 --> 00:02:46.992
Four — heavy is engineered for; brittle is stronger than granite.

7.1
00:02:46.992 --> 00:02:50.270
Seven objections, seven confident answers.

7.2
00:02:50.270 --> 00:02:53.548
Quiz time.

